  .container.container-small.margin-t-enormous
    %h1
      What is Kubeless?
    .row.collapse-b-tablet
      .col-12
        %p
          Kubeless is a Kubernetes-native serverless framework that lets you deploy small bits of
          code (functions) without having to worry about the underlying infrastructure. It is
          designed to be deployed on top of a Kubernetes cluster and take advantage of all the
          great Kubernetes primitives. If you are looking for an open source serverless solution
          that clones what you can find on AWS Lambda, Azure Functions, and Google Cloud Functions,
          Kubeless is for you!
        %p
          Kubeless Includes:
        %ul
          %li
            Support for Python, Node.js, Ruby, PHP, Golang, .NET, Ballerina and custom runtimes
          %li
            CLI compliant with AWS Lambda CLI
          %li
            Event triggers using Kafka messaging system and HTTP events
          %li
            Prometheus monitoring of functions calls and function latency by default
          %li
            = link_to 'Serverless', 'https://serverless.com', rel: 'noopener', target: '_blank'
            Framework
            = link_to 'plugin', 'https://github.com/serverless/serverless-kubeless',
                      rel: 'noopener', target: '_blank'

  %section.gradient-45-accent.padding-v-enormous.margin-t-giant.elevation-1
    .container
      .row.align-center.collapse-b-tablet
        .col-5
          %h3.type-color-iron How does it work? Check it out!
          %p.type-color-iron
            Kubeless uses a
            = link_to 'Custom Resource Definition', |
                      'https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/access-kubernetes-api/extend-api-' + |
                      'custom-resource-definitions/', rel: 'noopener', target: '_blank', |
                      class: 'type-color-action' |
            to be able to create functions as custom
            kubernetes resources. It then runs an in-cluster controller that watches these custom
            resources and launches runtimes on-demand. The controller dynamically injects the
            functions code into the runtimes and make them available over HTTP or via a PubSub
            mechanism.
        .col-1
        .col-6
          %iframe{src:"https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/AxZuQIJUX4s?rel=0&amp;showinfo=0",
                  frameborder: "0", allowfullscreen: true, width:"100%", height:"315",
                  class: 'elevation-3'}

